cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.SI

The paper discusses concentration of measure inequalities and their applications in information theory, communications, and coding theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions functional analysis and high-dimensional statistics, which are related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), respectively. The paper also discusses the martingale method, which is related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and the transportation-cost inequalities, which are related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
